Comfortdelgro Corporation says Kua Hong Pak will step down as group Chief Executive Officer
Wednesday, 26 Apr 2017 05:09am EDT 
April 26 (Reuters) - Comfortdelgro Corporation Ltd :Kua Hong Pak will step down as Managing Director/Group Chief Executive Officer.Yang Ban Seng will be appointed as Managing Director/Group Chief Executive Officer. 
			
Full Article





Cabcharge Australia to divest CDC bus joint venture stake to Comfortdelgro Corp
Tuesday, 20 Dec 2016 05:58pm EST 
Cabcharge Australia Ltd  : Sale consideration for cabcharge's 49% interest in cdc is $186 million . Reached an agreement to sell its 49% stake in cdc to partner Comfortdelgro for $186 million subject to firb approval . Net proceeds to cabcharge are expected to be $183 million .Cabcharge to divest cdc bus joint venture stake for $186m-cab.ax. 
			
Full Article





Comfortdelgro says qtrly revenue S$1.02 bln
Friday, 12 Aug 2016 05:05am EDT 
Comfortdelgro Corporation Ltd : Tax-exempt one-tier interim dividend of 4.25 cents per ordinary share has been declared" . Qtrly revenue s$1.02 billion versus s$ 1.04 billion . Revenue from the rail business is expected to increase with higher ridership from downtown line 2. . Revenue from the taxi business is expected to be maintained. . Bus revenue in Singapore is expected to be maintained . Revenue from the driving centre business is expected to be maintained. . Revenue from the inspection and testing services business is expected to be lower. . Q2 profit attributable to shareholders of the company s$85.2 million versus s$80.9 million . Revenue from the bus station business in guangzhou is expected to be lower . Revenue from the car rental and leasing business is expected to be maintained. . "Costs, in particular staff costs, are expected to be higher." . 
			
